<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:31PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Judith
Basin and west central Fergus Counties through 200 PM MDT...
At 131 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Denton, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Danvers.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
